<header>
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Exercise 1</h1>
    <h2>User Profiles</h2>
  </div>
</header>
<div class="a11y-exercise">
  <contentinfo role="contentinfo">
    <h1>Learning Objectives</h1>
    <div class="a11y-exercise-learning-objectives">
      <ol>
        <li>
          Given an ember component and its relevant test, a developer should be able to use the ember-a11y-testing
          framework to assert that no a11y violations exist.
        </li>
        <li>
          Given an ember acceptance test, a developer should be able to use the ember-a11y-testing
          framework to assert that no a11y violations exist.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
    <h1>Instructions</h1>
    <div class="a11y-exercise-instructions">
      <ol>
        <li>
          <p>Run the tests for this exercise: <code>ember test -server -f "Exercise 1"</code>.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          Add an a11y audit to the component's integration test.
        </li>
        <li>
          Fix any accessibility violations found in the component's test.
        </li>
        <li>
          Add an a11y audit to the component's integration test.
        </li>
        <li>
          Fix any accessibility violations found in the acceptance test.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </contentinfo>
  <main>
    <h1>Results</h1>
    <div class="a11y-exercise-results">
      <ul class="user-profiles-list">
        {{#each model as |user|}}
          <li class="user-profiles-list-item">
            {{user-profile user=user}}
          </li>
        {{/each}}
      </ul>
    </div>
  </main>
</div>